{"level":40,"time":1774396296864,"pid":78802,"hostname":"Mac-mini.lan","err":{"type":"RequestError","message":"Unprocessable Entity: \"Line could not be resolved\" - https://docs.github.com/rest/pulls/reviews#create-a-review-for-a-pull-request","stack":"HttpError: Unprocessable Entity: \"Line could not be resolved\" - https://docs.github.com/rest/pulls/reviews#create-a-review-for-a-pull-request\n    at fetchWrapper (file:///Users/ironsha/Desktop/projects/ironsha/node_modules/@octokit/request/dist-bundle/index.js:122:11)\n    at process.processTicksAndRejections (node:internal/process/task_queues:104:5)\n    at async postReview (/Users/ironsha/Desktop/projects/ironsha/src/github/review-poster.ts:23:7)\n    at async runReviewPipeline (/Users/ironsha/Desktop/projects/ironsha/src/review/pipeline.ts:311:7)","name":"HttpError","status":422,"request":{"method":"POST","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/shamwow/openarena/pulls/1/reviews","headers":{"accept":"application/vnd.github.v3+json","user-agent":"octokit-rest.js/21.1.1 octokit-core.js/6.1.6 Node.js/25","authorization":"token [REDACTED]","content-type":"application/json; charset=utf-8"},"body":{"body":"This PR converts enums to const objects for erasableSyntaxOnly, fixes TypeScript/ESLint errors, and adds AGENTS.md + README updates. Build and lint pass. The code changes are mostly mechanical (enum→const, removing unused params) with a few substantive fixes worth noting.\n\n---\n<sub>reviewer | thread::262729bc-0b88-45c1-ab52-d611b66e0a54 | review::e7df990a-5fb2-4ecd-a339-d4fbecace9ff</sub>","event":"REQUEST_CHANGES","comments":[{"path":"src/cards/sets/starter/creatures.ts","line":146,"body":"**Bug: Mismatched variable name and card name.** `InfernalPlunge` is the export name but the card is `'Inferno Titan'` with id `'inferno-titan'`. This will be confusing for anyone importing this card — the export should be `InfernoTitan` to match the actual card definition.\n\n---\n<sub>reviewer | thread::ccf68ad5-8ceb-4ad7-82f7-5c2585047710 | review::e7df990a-5fb2-4ecd-a339-d4fbecace9ff</sub>"},{"path":"src/cards/sets/starter/creatures.ts","line":129,"body":"**No-op ability handler.** Shivan Dragon's activated ability `() => {}` spends {R} mana but does nothing — the comment says it's deferred to continuous effects, but no continuous effect is actually registered. This means players can pay mana for zero effect. Consider either implementing the +1/+0 buff or removing the activated ability until it works.\n\n---\n<sub>reviewer | thread::26ca3bc7-a35f-49ba-b616-7f3172141029 | review::e7df990a-5fb2-4ecd-a339-d4fbecace9ff</sub>"},{"path":"src/ui/hooks/useGameEngine.ts","line":62,"body":"**Missing useEffect cleanup.** `createEngine` subscribes to engine callbacks (`onStateChange`, `onGameLog`, `onChoiceRequest`) but the `useEffect` has no cleanup function. If this component ever remounts (React Strict Mode in dev does this), you'll get duplicate subscriptions and state updates from a stale engine. Return a cleanup that unsubscribes or disposes the old engine:\n```ts\nuseEffect(() => {\n  const engine = createEngine(setState, setLegalActions, setGameLog, setPendingChoice);\n  engineRef.current = engine;\n  return () => { engine.dispose(); }; // or similar cleanup\n}, []);\n```\n\n---\n<sub>reviewer | thread::6e59f6da-58a0-4d5f-9b16-6acd1bd39055 | review::e7df990a-5fb2-4ecd-a339-d4fbecace9ff</sub>"},{"path":"src/ui/hooks/useGameEngine.ts","line":83,"body":"**Same cleanup issue in `newGame`.** When `newGame` creates a fresh engine, the old engine's subscriptions are never torn down. The old engine's `onStateChange` callback still holds references to the React setters and will continue firing if anything triggers it. The old engine should be explicitly cleaned up before creating a new one.\n\n---\n<sub>reviewer | thread::ef9c21b3-891e-4df5-bc14-df889cecd691 | review::e7df990a-5fb2-4ecd-a339-d4fbecace9ff</sub>"},{"path":"src/engine/StackManager.ts","line":115,"body":"**Unused parameter `_triggeringEvent`.** This parameter is received but never used in `putTriggeredAbility`. If it's not needed now, consider removing it from the signature rather than prefixing with `_` — the triggering event is important context for a triggered ability (e.g., to get the event's details for 'whenever X, do Y based on X'). If it will be needed soon, a TODO comment explaining the planned usage would help.\n\n---\n<sub>reviewer | thread::d9e7c9a2-3726-45f0-8bff-5b2e223b45e4 | review::e7df990a-5fb2-4ecd-a339-d4fbecace9ff</sub>"},{"path":"src/engine/ManaManager.ts","line":249,"body":"**Unused parameter `_state: GameState`.** The `autoTapForCost` method accepts `_state` but never uses it, relying entirely on the `battlefield` array and `player` id. Either use it (e.g., to check game state conditions) or remove it to keep the API honest.\n\n---\n<sub>reviewer | thread::54c3fdfd-ec45-4b07-b7e9-af3d1ab67a91 | review::e7df990a-5fb2-4ecd-a339-d4fbecace9ff</sub>"}]},"request":{}},"response":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/shamwow/openarena/pulls/1/reviews","status":422,"headers":{"access-control-allow-origin":"*","access-control-expose-headers":"ETag, Link, Location, Retry-After, X-GitHub-OTP, X-RateLimit-Limit, X-RateLimit-Remaining, X-RateLimit-Used, X-RateLimit-Resource, X-RateLimit-Reset, X-OAuth-Scopes, X-Accepted-OAuth-Scopes, X-Poll-Interval, X-GitHub-Media-Type, X-GitHub-SSO, X-GitHub-Request-Id, Deprecation, Sunset","content-length":"189","content-security-policy":"default-src 'none'","content-type":"application/json; charset=utf-8","date":"Tue, 24 Mar 2026 23:51:36 GMT","referrer-policy":"origin-when-cross-origin, strict-origin-when-cross-origin","server":"github.com","strict-transport-security":"max-age=31536000; includeSubdomains; preload","vary":"Accept-Encoding, Accept, X-Requested-With","x-accepted-oauth-scopes":"","x-content-type-options":"nosniff","x-frame-options":"deny","x-github-api-version-selected":"2022-11-28","x-github-media-type":"github.v3; format=json","x-github-request-id":"3CA6:1EF208:15E14:5D6FA:69C32388","x-oauth-scopes":"read:org, repo","x-ratelimit-limit":"5000","x-ratelimit-remaining":"4980","x-ratelimit-reset":"1774399486","x-ratelimit-resource":"core","x-ratelimit-used":"20","x-xss-protection":"0"},"data":{"message":"Unprocessable Entity","errors":["Line could not be resolved"],"documentation_url":"https://docs.github.com/rest/pulls/reviews#create-a-review-for-a-pull-request","status":"422"}}},"msg":"Batch review failed, retrying comments individually"}
